<HEADLINE> Japanese Helping on Chinese Solar-Energy Power Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Work on a solar-energy power station
was completed today and it started generating electricity for a
primary school in a suburb of the Tibetan regional capital of
Lhasa.
</P>
<P>
A Japanese new energy research and development institute helped
the power station as part of solar energy cooperative project
between China and Japan to help China's less-developed areas.
</P>
<P>
Tibet has plenty of solar energy resources and Japan has a
great deal of experience in the use of solar energy, according to
a local official, who says that China and Japan will continue to
cooperate in building power projects in Tibet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
